From the Unborn Zhang:\line Wisdom dawns when you relax in not knowing, the natural state does not arrive when you think. For example, iron cannot be commanded to run away, as it is not endowed with reason. But an ignorant cow herder can abandon thinking easily and gain understanding though yoga. Remain without attachments, like a dog's corpse. Remain without desire, like a person who is ill. Like a brahmin spinning thread, relax at ease in the wisdom of yoga. Remain free of fixations, like a corpse. Remain mindless, like a crazy person. Remain in clarity, like a crystal. Remain without pretense like a small child. Keep a relaxed focus on what needs to be done now. This is the explanation on how to settle the mind. }
