From Jetsun Tilopa:\line To see completely, abandon all physical activities and rest easily the natural state. See ordinary speech as sound-emptiness, similar to an echo. View all phenomena without the aid of mental deliberation. Regard the body as hollow, like a reed. Go beyond the conceptual realm and regard the mind as like the empty vault of the sky. Relax within that and reject all verbal designations as unreal.\line Also:\line No mind is beyond all ambition. The self-arisen nature is like drawing on water. If you do not dwell or apprehend, you will not transgress the ultimate meaning. Do not veil yourself in ignorance and you will not transgress your samaya. If finally, you are beyond all aspirations, the meaning of all the baskets of scriptures without exception will be seen. Be diligent and strive to liberate yourself from samsara. The benefit is that this meditative equipoise will burn up all defilements and obscurations. Thus the torch bearer of the teachings has explained it. \line Also he said:\line The shifting emotions of attachment and aversion are the realm of samsara. Cut them all off. Meditative cultivation does not depend on being alone at the foot of a tree or in a mountain retreat. Meditation is something that is established within yourself. The attainment of non-attainment is Mahamudra. That also he said. }
